1:You can do "make" and get nandflash.bin;

2:There are some commands:
-->loadb:you can load any file from you pc to nandflash(if it is enough to hold it);
-->help:there are some information you may need;
-->flashl:load data from nandflash to mem;
-->flashw:program data from mem to nandflash;
-->dma:play music in dma-mod(if there is any music base block 2);
-->go:execute from 0x31000000
-->md:print information at addr 0x00000000;

Example:

TWave $help
--TWave--HELP--
s3c2440 help manual
-flashw-        program data from mem to nandflash
-flashl-        load data from nandflash to mem
-dma-   play music in dma-mod(if there is any music base block 2)

TWave $loadb

TWave $flashw

TWave $flashl

TWave $dma

3:if any bugs, you can e_mail us:
